Sketch of solution (brief):

- The numbers lie on hexagonal rings. The last number on ring k is L(k)=1+3k(k+1). Solve 1+3k(k+1) ≥ 2026 to get k = 26. Ring 26 runs from 1952 to 2107, so 2026 is the 75th element of ring 26 (1952 + 74).

- Using axial coordinates with neighbours
  NW=(0,-1), W=(-1,0), SW=(-1,1), SE=(0,1), E=(1,0), NE=(1,-1),
  the start of ring k is at (k,0). Following the spiral ordering gives that 2026 is at coordinate (−22,−4).

- Its six neighbours lie at
  (−21,−5), (−21,−4), (−22,−3), (−23,−3), (−23,−4), (−22,−5).
  These belong respectively to rings 26, 25, 25, 26, 27, 27.

- Converting these coordinates back to their numbers (by the same “start at (r,0) and count along the ring” method) gives the neighbour values
  2025, 1873, 1874, 2027, 2184, 2185.

- Summing them: 2025+1873+1874+2027+2184+2185 = 12168.
